<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb7bc97d9-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s577"><num value="577">§ 577.</num><heading> Arbitrators</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idb7bc97da-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s577/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> The parties to an arbitration proceeding shall be entitled to participate in the selection of the arbitrator.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idb7bc97db-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s577/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> The arbitrator shall be a neutral who meets the criteria of <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s573">section 573 of this title</ref>.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idb7bc97dc-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/101/552/s4/b">Pub. L. 101–552, § 4(b)</ref>, <date date="1990-11-15">Nov. 15, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/2742">104 Stat. 2742</ref>, § 587; renumbered § 577 and amended <ref href="/us/pl/102/354/s3/b/2">Pub. L. 102–354, § 3(b)(2)</ref>, (3), <date date="1992-08-26">Aug. 26, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/944">106 Stat. 944</ref>, 945.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb7bc97dd-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">
